Another issue related to symlink resolution, in addition to what @ClassicLimeBuzzard298 mentioned: relative symlink targets should be evaluated relative to the symlink's parent dir, not to the symlink itself. In practice this means that when we call resolvePath for a symlink target, the base path should be the symlink location with the last segment removed.

